flax@frej.teknikum.uu.se (Jonas Flygare) writes:
>Several years ago (1985-1987, I _think_ but I'm not sure) there was a 
>posting about a knapsack cipher method, that was almost immediately
>cancelled. I had it saved before the cancel, but have lost my copy..
>I know it's a slim chance, but if _anyone_ remembers, and have a copy
>or pointer I'd appreciate it _very_ much. 

       That was an early attempt at a public-key system, but someone
figured out how to break knapsack cyphers, so there's not much interest
in them.  If you have Berkeley UNIX source, you can see one in the old
"secretmail" system (xsend, xget, enroll).

